    "text": "Erdős Problem #462: declared status 'open'. Formalized: no. Let $p(n)$ denote the least prime factor of $n$. There is a constant $c>0$ such that\\[\\sum_{\\substack{n<x\\\\ n\\textrm{ not prime}}}\\frac{p(n)}{n}\\sim c\\frac{x^{1/2}}{(\\log x)^2}.\\]Is it true that there exists a constant $C>0$ such that\\[\\sum_{x\\leq n\\leq x+Cx^{1/2}(\\log x)^2}\\frac{p(n)}{n} \\gg 1\\]for all large $x$? Prize: no. OEIS: A032742. Tags: number theory, primes.",
